race.comment: Anything could win this tricky little race. VEGA MAGNIFICO (6) went to the lead in a change of tactics last start but was beaten at the furlong in a BM84 over this distance at Caulfield. Comes home to find an easier race today. Best form puts him in top - five unplaced runs from five Rosehill appearances the worrying stat. GOD'S WINDOW (2) has been ridden cold and failed to land a glove in his two runs this prep. Up a little in distance and back in class might be the recipe for a return to form. TASTULA (8) dug deep to just prevail in a Canterbury midweeker recently. Harder this time but can keep improving at just the third run of the prep. POCKETING (3) disappointed last Saturday over the mile. Class runner worth another chance.
